[{"question":"From what you\u0027ve been hearing, Ed, from your sources, consistent with everything that is now building up about the reality of the horror that went on in that house?","answer":"That does go along with the fact that I\u0027m hearing that Ariel Castro had a hierarchy.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":35,"aSentId":36},{"question":"Is that right?","answer":"That\u0027s right.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":43,"aSentId":44},{"question":"What do you make of that?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m hearing from the interrogation that he really didn\u0027t deny anything, but he didn\u0027t admit it.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":53,"aSentId":54},{"question":"I mean, this is a defense that\u0027s going to be extremely difficult to sustain itself, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, it is.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":59,"aSentId":60},{"question":"What was your reaction, when you first heard that Ariel Castro, the father of the man that you were married to, had been arrested in connection with this awful crime, series of crimes, what was your reaction?","answer":"I was shocked.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":70,"aSentId":71},{"question":"What kind of man -- what kind of man was he?","answer":"I never had the desire to get to know him personally or very closely.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":75,"aSentId":76},{"question":"And he also beat your ex-husband repeatedly when he was younger, is that right?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":92,"aSentId":93},{"question":"What was the experience of being in that house with Ariel Castro like?","answer":"It\u0027s much like everyone else describes.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":100,"aSentId":101},{"question":"Have you talked to your ex-husband since the revelations of a week ago?","answer":"No.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":115,"aSentId":116},{"question":"Did you believe them when you saw their interview?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":120,"aSentId":121},{"question":"Do you think the scale of what he was doing even then warranted more attention?","answer":"Oh, well, definitely, but I mean, I wish they had, but I can see how perhaps not.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":146,"aSentId":147},{"question":"Did you know her?","answer":"No.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":156,"aSentId":157},{"question":"But you never encountered her?","answer":"I don\u0027t believe so, or if I did, it wasn\u0027t in any, you know, lasting capacity.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":160,"aSentId":161},{"question":"What is your overriding reaction?","answer":"Just anguish.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":169,"aSentId":170},{"question":"Dana, this is a right old mess for the president, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"That\u0027s certainly one way to put it.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":202,"aSentId":203},{"question":"Now, where and how is that line drawn, and how far over it from this report do we think they crossed?","answer":"That\u0027s absolutely right.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":238,"aSentId":239},{"question":"Has the White House handled this properly, do you think?","answer":"Well, maybe B-plus but I\u0027m mystified by the legalistic language.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":255,"aSentId":256},{"question":"Is it really feasible, do you think, that the IRS would independently be so overtly political against the Republicans and Tea Party in particular without anybody at the White House having at least had a quiet word?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":264,"aSentId":265},{"question":"Should there be proof that emerges that somebody at the White House knew that the IRS were targeting the Tea Party and so on, how serious would that be?","answer":"First of all, I think it\u0027s a crime.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":288,"aSentId":289},{"question":"Does that in itself justify what they did in terms of basically going after the Associated Press and potentially checking the records of up to 100 journalists?","answer":"Well, full disclosure, I\u0027m not only a friend but a great admirer of Eric Holder\u0027s for many, many years.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":302,"aSentId":303},{"question":"And I suppose it really comes down to was what they did actually legal?","answer":"Well, there is a ground for subpoenaing documents.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":312,"aSentId":313},{"question":"And I think they have a right to do that, don\u0027t they?","answer":"Well, they certainly did remove those references, whether they were removed by the CIA or whether they were removed by people in the State Department is unclear.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":333,"aSentId":334},{"question":"Why not communicate that right up front?","answer":"I agree with you.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":343,"aSentId":344},{"question":"I think you put it all together with the IRS targeting the Tea Party, the Benghazi issue of these talking points and al Qaeda references being removed, the A.P. being targeted by the Justice Department, in what many consider to be an outrageous manner -- you put it all together, and you have a real breach of trust in President Obama and his administration, don\u0027t you?","answer":"So look, yes, there\u0027s a breach of trust because of the opaqueness of the way the White House has handled it, at least starting with the talking points.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":346,"aSentId":347},{"question":"That eliminates a lot of people, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"It can.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":421,"aSentId":422},{"question":"Is that one of the wonders of modern science, if you like?","answer":"It is.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":450,"aSentId":451},{"question":"Just one last question, Dr. Sussman: do you believe, from your medical perspective, that this simple op-ed piece and the worldwide reaction can save a lot of lives?","answer":"I think she did tremendous goodwill and good work on behalf of women worldwide.","docId":"130514pmt","qSentId":466,"aSentId":467}]